eration intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: jline:jline:2.14.6\\nStage: metadata_fix_failed\\n\\n## Summary\\nThe post-generation failure was caused by a single generated native test, `TerminalLineSettingsTest.constructorUsesInheritedInputWhenAConsoleProviderIsAvailable()`. This was **not** a reachability-metadata failure.\\n\\nThe failing assertion was `assertThat(System.console()).isNotNull()`. In the native-image test process, `System.console()` remained `null`, so the test failed before any missing-registration error occurred.\\n\\n## Root cause\\nThis failure was caused by a runtime/environment assumption in the generated test, not by missing metadata:\\n\\n- The test assumes the native test executable has an inherited interactive console available.\\n- The Gradle failure excerpt shows a plain assertion failure, not a `MissingReflectionRegistrationError`, `MissingResourceRegistrationError`, or any other metadata-related error.\\n- The Codex log shows follow-up attempts to force console-provider access through internal JDK console classes and extra `--add-exports` / `--add-opens` settings. That confirms the problem was tied to console-provider/runtime behavior in native image, not unresolved reachability metadata.\\n\\nBecause this is a non-metadata failure, the correct intervention was to remove the generated test instead of preserving it and asking for more metadata.\\n\\n## Changes made\\nRemoved the generated test and its test-only scaffolding:\\n\\n- `tests/src/jline/jline/2.14.6/src/test/java/org/graalvm/jline/TerminalLineSettingsTest.java`\\n- `tests/src/jline/jline/2.14.6/src/test/resources/junit-platform.properties`\\n- test-only console access flags that had been added to `tests/src/jline/jline/2.14.6/build.gradle`\\n\\nNo metadata files were modified.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\nThe rest of the generated support is still valid and useful:\\n\\n- the remaining generated native tests pass for `jline:jline:2.14.6`\\n- the preserved tests still exercise real library behavior around resource loading, signal handling, reflective terminal loading, HawtJNI native library loading, and OSv terminal integration\\n- the current generated metadata support is still needed for those passing scenarios and should not be discarded just because the console-dependent test made an invalid runtime assumption\\n\\n## Verification\\nAfter removing the console-dependent test, the library passed again with:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=jline:jline:2.14.6`\"\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:3104:      \"input_tokens_used\": 507836,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:3105:      \"cached_input_tokens_used\": 6025344,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:3108:      \"cost_usd\": 2.4405,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:3109:      \"generated_loc\": 450,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:3120:    \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-23T15:11:51Z\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:3123:    \"status\": \"failure\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:3125:      \"input_tokens_used\": 38902,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:3126:      \"output_tokens_used\": 10063,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/184