ibrary_support.json:4371:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.codehaus.woodstox:stax2-api:4.2.2\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nBoth failing native tests had the same root cause: this was a metadata-related failure, not a bad test and not a native-image platform limitation. `XMLValidationSchemaFactory.newInstance(...)` looks up a custom service definition resource at `META-INF/services/org.codehaus.stax2.validation.XMLValidationSchemaFactory.dtd`. In the failing native image, that resource was not registered, so runtime lookup returned no provider and both tests failed with `FactoryConfigurationError`.\\n\\n## Failure breakdown\\n\\n### `loadsFactoryFromSystemResourcesWhenNoClassLoaderIsProvided()`\\n- **Root cause:** missing native-image resource metadata for `META-INF/services/org.codehaus.stax2.validation.XMLValidationSchemaFactory.dtd`\\n- **Why it failed:** the null-classloader path falls back to system resource lookup, but the service file was not embedded in the native image, so no `XMLValidationSchemaFactory` implementation could be found.\\n\\n### `loadsFactoryFromExplicitClassLoaderResources()`\\n- **Root cause:** same missing native-image resource metadata\\n- **Why it failed:** even with the explicit test class loader, the same service file was absent from the native image, so provider discovery failed in the same way.\\n\\n## Codex log findings\\n\\nThe Codex log shows this was already identified correctly as a metadata gap. Codex added a resource entry for:\\n\\n- `META-INF/services/org.codehaus.stax2.validation.XMLValidationSchemaFactory.dtd`\\n\\nwith condition:\\n\\n- `org.codehaus.stax2.validation.XMLValidationSchemaFactory`\\n\\nAfter that change, Codex reran `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.codehaus.woodstox:stax2-api:4.2.2 --stacktrace` and both native tests passed.\\n\\n## Remaining missing metadata\\n\\nNone. The log indicates the metadata issue was resolved by registering the service resource. There is no evidence of a remaining reflection or JNI gap behind this failure.\\n\\n## Intervention decision\\n\\n- **Did not remove any generated tests.**\\n- **Did not modify metadata files in this intervention.**\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe generated support is still valuable because it covers a real native-image compatibility requirement in `stax2-api`: runtime discovery of `XMLValidationSchemaFactory` implementations through a custom `META-INF/services/...dtd` resource. The generated test and its service file validate both lookup variants exercised by the API:\\n\\n- system-resource lookup when no class loader is provided\\n- explicit class-loader resource lookup\\n\\nRemoving that generated support would discard legitimate coverage for a real metadata requirement that Codex already fixed.\"\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:4375:      \"cached_input_tokens_used\": 504448,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:4378:      \"cost_usd\": 0.2645,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:4379:      \"generated_loc\": 111,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:4381:      \"metadata_entries\": 0,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:4382:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 0.93\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:4390:    \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-22T04:28:45.655179Z\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/184