emoving the two failing native-only tests.\\n\\n## Failure analysis\\n\\n### 1. `org.jboss.logmanager.LogManagerTest > readConfigurationFallsBackToLogManagerClassLoaderWhenContextClassLoaderRejectsConfigurator()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** `LogManager.construct(...)` uses `Class.forName(name, true, contextClassLoader)` first and then falls back to the `LogManager` class loader. In the native image, the assertion `rejectingClassLoader.rejectedClassLoadAttempted` stayed `false`, even though the configurator was still instantiated successfully.\\n- **Interpretation:** this test depends on observing a custom `ClassLoader.loadClass(...)` rejection path for an image-contained class. That is a native-image class-loading behavior difference, not missing metadata. If metadata were missing, the failure would have been a registration error or reflective instantiation failure, not a plain `assertThat(...).isTrue()` failure.\\n- **Action taken:** removed that test method and its test-only helpers from `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/LogManagerTest.java`.\\n\\n### 2. `org.jboss.logmanager.formatters.Formatters12Test > extendedExceptionFormattingUsesClassLoadingFallbacksAndClassResourceLookup()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** the native failure was again a boolean assertion (`loadedFromBytes`, `rejectedSystemTargetAttempted`, or `classResourceRequested`) staying `false`, not a missing registration error. This test tries to verify that `%E` formatting forces a custom context class loader to byte-define a target class and then performs `.class` resource lookup through that loader.\\n- **Interpretation:** the formatter output path is preserved, but the test relies on runtime-observable custom class loading and resource lookup behavior that native image does not preserve in the same way for image-contained classes. The native image already built successfully, so this is not evidence of missing metadata.\\n- **Action taken:** removed that test method and the test-only helper loader/classes that existed solely for it from `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/formatters/Formatters12Test.java`.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support still exercises meaningful `jboss-logmanager` behavior that is relevant to reachability metadata:\\n\\n- context-class-loader-based configurator and locator instantiation still has coverage\\n- bootstrap fallback for exception formatting still has coverage\\n- privileged exception class resource lookup still has coverage\\n- property-based handler/filter/formatter/error-manager configuration still has coverage\\n- serialization-related coverage for the map implementations still has coverage\\n- default configuration lookup and typed array handling still have coverage\\n\\nIn short, only the two tests that depended on native-image-incompatible custom class-loading observability were removed. The rest of the generated suite still validates real library behavior and should be preserved.\"\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5129:      \"iterations\": 10,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5131:      \"generated_loc\": 718,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5137:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/AtomicArrayTest.java\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1844-aaab825a/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5138:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanag