adata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5204:          \"ratio\": 0.260381,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5209:          \"missed\": 601,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5210:          \"ratio\": 0.235369,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5217:      \"intervention_file\": \"post-gen-interventions/org.jboss.logmanager_jboss-logmanager_1.2.0.GA.md\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5218:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe post-generation failures had two different causes:\\n\\n1. `ConcurrentReferenceHashMapTest.serializationRoundTripPreservesEntries()` in the Codex metadata-fix log was **metadata-related**.\\n2. `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()` in the final Gradle failure was **not metadata-related**; it depended on JVM class-loader fallback behavior that does not hold under Native Image.\\n\\nI removed the generated `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()` test and kept the rest of the generated support.\\n\\n## Failure analysis\\n\\n### 1. Codex log failure: metadata-related\\n\\nThe Codex log shows a `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` from:\\n\\n- `ConcurrentReferenceHashMapTest.serializationRoundTripPreservesEntries()`\\n\\nMissing entry reported by Native Image:\\n\\n- `java.util.concurrent.locks.ReentrantLock$Sync.readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream)`\\n\\nThat failure came from Java deserialization of `ConcurrentReferenceHashMap`, so it was a real reachability-metadata gap rather than a bad test. This support should be preserved because it covers an actual native-image requirement for the library's serialization path.\\n\\n### 2. Remaining Gradle failure: not metadata-related\\n\\nThe remaining failing test was:\\n\\n- `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()`\\n\\nThis failed on:\\n\\n- `assertThat(rejectingClassLoader.wasRejected()).isTrue()`\\n\\nRoot cause:\\n\\n- The test assumes the formatter will first try to resolve the stack-frame class through the thread context class loader, observe a `ClassNotFoundException`, and only then fall back to the caller loader.\\n- In Native Image, class resolution for already-linked image classes does not preserve that JVM class-loading interaction in the same way. The formatted stack trace is still produced, but the custom rejecting loader is never asked to load the class, so `wasRejected()` stays `false`.\\n- No `Missing*RegistrationError` was reported for this failure, so this was not a metadata problem.\\n\\nThis is therefore a Native Image class-loading/runtime-semantics issue in the generated test, and removing that generated test was the correct intervention.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe rest of the generated support still exercises real library behavior and should remain in place:\\n\\n- serialization coverage for `ConcurrentReferenceHashMap` and `FastCopyHashMap`\\n- resource lookup coverage for `DefaultConfigurationLocator`\\n- formatter/resource coverage in `Formatters12Test`\\n- configuration loading and component instantiation coverage in `LogManagerTest` and `PropertyConfiguratorTest`\\n\\nAfter removing only the non-metadata-related formatter fallback test, the coordinate passed again with:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA`\\n- `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA`\\n\\nSo the generated metadata-backed support is still valuable and should be kept; only the unsupported caller-loader fallback assertion needed to be dropped.\"\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5222:      \"cached_input_tokens_used\": 5017472,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5223:      \"output_tokens_used\": 76101,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5226:      \"generated_loc\": 704,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5227:      \"tested_library_loc\": 903,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5229:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 26.04\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5232:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org_jboss_logmanager/jboss_logmanager/LogManagerTest.java\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5233:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/reachability-metadata.json\"\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5237:    \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-17T20:16:35.872241Z\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5239:    \"starting_commit\": \"dc5bb2d3277f2cf3005c468383476ec86f7d01c2\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5240:    \"ending_commit\": \"f77416bd5af3da24a8ed8144e5574850d01dab02\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5250:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5255:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5263:          \"ratio\": 0.040144,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5264:          \"total\": 18907\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5268:          \"missed\": 4903,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5269:          \"ratio\": 0.043317,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5275:          \"ratio\": 0.039707,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5283:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.jboss.narayana.jta:jta:5.12.4.Final\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe native test failures were metadata-related, not caused by an unsupported Narayana feature, a test bug, or a platform limitation that would justify deleting generated tests.\\n\\nThe Codex log shows that the generated support was incomplete during the metadata-fix loop. In particular, the two serialization-focused tests needed test-only serialization metadata, and removing them would have thrown away valid coverage for real native-image requirements.\\n\\n## Failure-by-failure root cause\\n\\n### `JNDIManagerTest.bindTransactionSynchronizationRegistryImplementationUsesConfiguredClass()`\\n\\n- The Gradle failure excerpt showed reflective instantiation of `com.arjuna.ats.jta.common.JTAEnvironmentBean` failing through `BeanPopulator`.\\n- That is a metadata-style failure path: Narayana creates its environment beans reflectively, so native-image needs the constructor path to remain available.\\n- This is **not** evidence of a bad generated test. It exercises normal library behavior used by `JNDIManager`.\\n- In the later Codex/native rerun, this test passed, so it should be preserved.\\n\\n### `XAOnePhaseResourceTest.packAndUnpackSerializableXaResource()`\\n\\n- The remaining Codex log shows this was failing because native-image did not have complete serialization registration for the serialized state used by the test.\\n- Codex added test-only `serialization-config.json` entries for the custom serializable fixtures, but the next rerun still failed because Narayana also serialized a `java.lang.String` field inside that object graph.\\n- Root cause: **incomplete test-only serialization metadata**, not an unsupported native-image behavior.\\n- This test should be preserved because it validates real serialization behavior inside `XAOnePhaseResource.pack/unpack`.\\n\\n### `XAResourceRecordTest.saveAndRestoreStateWithSerializableXaResource()`\\n\\n- This failed for the same reason as `XAOnePhaseResourceTest`: the serialized object graph used by `XAResourceRecord.save_state/restore_state` needed complete serialization registration.\\n- The Codex log shows the failure narrowing to missing serialization constructor support, which is metadata-related.\\n- The earlier excerpt also showed reflective/environment initialization issues while entering Narayana state-management code; those are consistent with the same metadata-fix workflow being incomplete rather than a test defect.\\n- This test should be preserved because it covers real native-image-sensitive behavior in `XAResourceRecord` state save/restore.\\n\\n## Why the generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support is valid and should stay because it enables genuine native-image coverage instead of masking a bad test:\\n\\n- `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/org.jboss.narayana.jta.jta.tests/serialization-config.json` is required for the two serialization-based tests.\\n- Those tests exercise real Narayana code paths that serialize and deserialize XA-related state.\\n- Deleting the tests would reduce coverage of legitimate native-image requirements for this library.\\n\\n## Outcome\\n\\nNo generated tests were removed.\\n\\nAfter preserving the generated test-only serialization support, the focused native lane succeeds:\\n\\n- `./gradlew nativeTest -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.narayana.jta:jta:5.12.4.Final --stacktrace`\\n\\nSo the correct intervention here is to **keep** the generated tests and preserve the generated test-only support rather than delete coverage.\"\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5287:      \"cached_input_tokens_used\": 3102464,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5291:      \"generated_loc\": 316,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5302:    \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-17T00:30:48Z\",\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5310:      \"cost_usd\": 0.4473,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:5311:      \"generated_loc\": 220,\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_rep